name: Kumbuh Jungle
address: Jalan Desa, Jehem, Kec. Tembuku, Kabupaten Bangli, Bali 80671, Indonesia
review 1:
Lived here for one night, although in photos it appears very beautiful and romantic, but in reality it is scary, specially in night time.
Fact is it is located in dense forest, no fencing installed in all side of property, it is open from forest side, which makes is unsafe. Moreover there is no gate latches and gates are always open.
Although staff is polite, food taste is good, but there is no one available in case of emergency in night time and In night there is a constant sound from wild insects and reptiles. There are a lot of lizards. Although the staff says that lizards are harmless, but they are scary.
Lizards roams on garden ground, pool wall, I don't know thy bite or not, but definitly it is scary.
I won't suggest it for honeymoon couple, specially if you have fear of insects and reptiles.
review 2:
Amazing place. Away from the city. Completely in the jungle.
The food was really good
The place was awesome
Little bit of cleaning with bed sheets and curtains must be maintained

review 4: Ah wow.. I celebrated my birthday at Kumbuh Jungle and it was so wonderful. Thank you to the whole team for making this day so special. The food was so delicious and thank you for the wonderful cake! They also prepared a romantic dinner, floating breakfast and candle lights around the Bamboo House. review 5: Beautiful place. Nice place too spend a quality time with your friends. And the service from Mas Ketut our Butler, is very excellent!
